cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE 

This paper deals with a notation for describing properties of relational structures, which is relevant to several areas of computer science. The use of lambda calculus and first-order logic suggests a connection to logic and automated reasoning (cs.LO), while the focus on databases and knowledge bases suggests a connection to database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The translation of an imperative language into the decidable fragment RL 2 suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
